<p><b>Loneliness</b> is a feeling where people experience a powerful surge of <a href="/wiki/Emptiness" title="Emptiness">emptiness</a> and solitude. Loneliness is more than the feeling of wanting <a href="/wiki/Interpersonal_relationship" title="Interpersonal relationship">company</a> or wanting to do something with another person. Someone who is lonely may find it hard to form human contact.</p>
<p>One of the first recorded uses of the word "lonely" was in <a href="/wiki/William_Shakespeare" title="William Shakespeare">William Shakespeare</a>'s <i><a href="/wiki/Coriolanus_(play)" title="Coriolanus (play)">Coriolanus</a></i>, Act IV Scene 1.</p>
